summary: This FBI Tactical Intelligence Report (TIR) summarizes information regarding a missing historical artifact (a bell) from the San Jose de Gracia Church in Trampas, New Mexico. The report notes witness allegations that the missing artifact may be located at the late Jeffrey Epstein's Zorro Ranch property in Stanley, New Mexico.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: The late Jeffrey Epstein is identified as the owner of Zorro Ranch in Stanley, New Mexico, where a missing historical artifact is alleged to be located.

events.title: Alleged Location of Missing Church Bell
events.description: Witness reporting alleges that a missing historical artifact (a bell) from the San Jose de Gracia Church may be found at Jeffrey Epstein's Zorro Ranch property.

locations: San Jose de Gracia Church, Trampas, New Mexico
keyFacts: The FBI document is a Tactical Intelligence Report (TIR) regarding a missing historical artifact.
The missing artifact is a bell from the San Jose de Gracia De Las Trampas mission church in New Mexico.
Witness allegations suggest the missing bell may be located at Jeffrey Epstein's Zorro Ranch property in Stanley, New Mexico.
The document indicates an FBI investigation into the potential location of stolen cultural property.
The report connects Epstein's New Mexico property to an alleged stolen artifact from a historical church.
